div.bibl:
lha mo sgrol ma’i mtshan brgya rtsa brgyad pa (
    Tāra­devī­nāmāṣṭa­śataka
). Toh 728, Degé Kangyur vol. 94 (rgyud, tsha), folios 219.a–222.a.

gloss.term:
Acts for which one will be reborn in hell immediately after death, without any intervening stages;
                                they are (1) killing one’s master or father, (2) killing one’s mother, (3) killing an arhat, (4) maliciously drawing
                                blood from a buddha, and (5) causing a schism in the saṅgha.
